Beautifully executed.  Without moving the king or interposing the queen Nc7+ snatches Ra8 for free.  Black can't seize it with the other rook since the queen is protecting it.

Counter.  The white queen could move to d6, losing that cool discovered check advantage.  Qd4 sacrifices the knight.

Mistake.  White can fork the rooks with Nc7.  Better would be Ne5, or Ne2+, followed by Rxc2 possibly.  Black must be careful about protecting g7 from Qxg7#, but coaxing white's f rook of the #1 rank yields QxRa1.

We anticipate Re7.  Counter threat with the black queen will cost black a rook (of his choice).  Ne5 suffers the same problem--the white queen moves to safety and black surrenders probably the "a" rook.  White could trade the queen for both rooks, but Qd6 looks better.
